<!-- WHY WRITE -->
<section class="section">
  <p class="label">Why write</p>
  <h2 class="section-title">What the project is looking for</h2>
  <p>Frida is not a project seeking visibility or a general support network. What interests the project is discussion about the real problems it is trying to solve.</p>
  <p>The following are welcome:</p>
  <ul style="margin: 1rem 0 1.25rem; line-height: 1.9;">
    <li>Critical reactions to published hypotheses</li>
    <li>Questions about architectural choices</li>
    <li>Proposals for collaboration on specific problems</li>
    <li>Indications of related work that has been overlooked or poorly handled</li>
    <li>Offers of documentary, conceptual or technical contribution</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Less relevant: requests for institutional partnership, commercial proposals, generic solicitations.</p>
</section>

<!-- PARTICIPATE -->
<section class="section">
  <p class="label">Contribute</p>
  <h2 class="section-title">The construction site is open</h2>
  <p>Frida is a demanding construction site, not a broadly collaborative project. Rigour takes precedence over numbers. That said, serious contributions from complementary backgrounds are actively sought.</p>

  <div class="participate">
    <p class="participate-title">Profiles sought</p>
    <p>The project sits at the crossroads of several disciplines. Contributions from any of the following directions are useful:</p>
    <div class="profiles">
      <span class="tag">Philosophy of language</span>
      <span class="tag">Hermeneutics</span>
      <span class="tag">Epistemology</span>
      <span class="tag">Language models</span>
      <span class="tag">Software architecture</span>
      <span class="tag">Memory systems</span>
      <span class="tag">Systems design</span>
      <span class="tag">Technical documentation</span>
      <span class="tag">Evaluation and benchmarking</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p>Contributions can take very different forms: critical reading of a document, proposing a more rigorous formulation of a hypothesis, implementing a module, building a test case, writing a synthesis note.</p>
  <p>The GitHub repository contains part of the project's open documentation:</p>

  <div class="btn-row">
    <a href="https://github.com/Tofmuck" class="btn btn-accent" target="_blank" rel="noopener">View the GitHub repository ↗</a>
    <a href="mailto:tofmuck@frida-ai.fr" class="btn">Write directly</a>
  </div>
</section>
